'''Bradford Burgess''' (born April 29, 1990 in [[Midlothian, Virginia]]) is an American professional [[basketball]] player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://basketball.eurobasket.com/player/Bradford_Burgess/163102 |title=Bradford Burgess <U+2013> Profile |work=Eurobasket.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> Burgess played four seasons for the [[VCU Rams men's basketball|VCU Rams]] team, from 2008 till 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/mens-college-basketball/player/_/id/41166/bradford-burgess |title=Bradford Burgess <U+2013> Profile |work=ESPN.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref>

==Professional career==
Burgess started his professional career in [[Belgium]] with the [[Stella Artois Leuven Bears]].<ref>{{cite web|author= Aaron Williams |url=http://rvanews.com/sports/vcu-lands-a-big-commit-bradford-burgess-gets-signed-and-season-tickets-are-still-hard-to-get/66330 |title=VCU lands a big commit, Bradford Burgess gets signed, and season tickets are still hard to get |work=RVANews |date=2012-09-05 |accessdate=2014-08-10}}</ref> He played two seasons in [[Leuven]].
